cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.NI, cs.PL 

The paper deals with the modeling and simulation of power flow variability in transmission networks, which involves the use of algorithms and techniques from the fields of control systems (cs.SY), distributed computing (cs.DC), electronic engineering (cs.ET), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and programming languages (cs.PL). The focus on probabilistic modeling and simulation also suggests a strong connection to the field of machine learning (cs.LG), but this is less likely given the specific context of the paper.
